Roles & Responsibilities
Project Civil Engineer
Civil projects bases (Utility diversion, trunk sewer, cycling path, bus facility works, Carparks, Tunnels)
Preferrable with LTA projects experiences

Primary Objective
Manage all aspects of an engineering project, form start to finish, so that it is completed on time and within budget.
Prepare project schedule, method statement, and follow up drawing
Plan, support and attend to site works progress, safety conducts, works procedure and quality.
Liaising with Project Manager & Director, LTA & government authorities, sub-con, clients & consultants.

Key Activities
Design, communicate and implement an operational plan for completing the project
Monitor progress and performance against the project plan
Take action to resolve operational problems and minimize delays
Identify, develop, and gather the resources necessary to complete the project. This may include preparing engineering standards, designs, and work specifications
Developing project schedules, budget, and forecasts; and selecting materials, equipment, and external contractors
Liaise with other operational areas in the organization (engineering, design, drafting, technical) to secure specialize resources and contributions for the project
Select, and manage the activities of outside contractors to ensure they are integrated into the project and that the organization receives satisfactory standards of service
Conduct project meetings and prepare regular reports to communicate the status of the project within and beyond the project team
Set priorities, allocate tasks, and coordinate project staff to meet projects targets and milestones.
Ensure smooth authority submission.
Solve technical issue such as drawing discrepancy, site condition changes etc.;
Checking plans, drawings and quantities for accuracy, raise RFI when necessary;
Ensure accuracy of setting out, levelling and site surveying;
Ensuring that all materials used and work performed are as per specifications;
Managing, monitoring and interpreting the contract design documents supplied by the client or architect;
Liaising with project consultants, architect, subcontractors, supervisors, planners, quantity surveyors and the general workforce involved in the project;
Support Project manager to liaise with the local authority (where appropriate to the project) to ensure compliance with local construction regulations and by-laws;
Liaising with clients and their representatives (architects, engineers and surveyors), including attending regular meetings to keep them informed of progress;
Overseeing quality control and assist safety department to achieve health and safety target on site;
Preparing method statement, daily weekly report. Assist preparing monthly report;
Raise the issue to Project Manager or Project Director if there is any unexpected technical problems, make feasible suggestion to solve the problem;
Ensuring all site inspection and record as per client/developer requirement
Ensuring all testing and quantity inspection are carried out as per contract requirement.

Requirement
BCA recognized Degree in Civil Engineering
Min 3 years Earthworks, Civil engineering working experiences, preferrable with LTA projects related

Roles & Responsibilities
Your duties as Site Engineer as follows:
setting out, leveling, and surveying the site;
checking plans, drawings, and quantities for accuracy of calculations;
ensuring all materials used and work performed are as per specifications;
overseeing the selection and requisition of materials and plant;
making cost-effective solutions and proposals for the intended project;
liaising with any consultants, subcontractors, supervisors, planners, quantity surveyors, and the general workforce involved in the project;
liaising with the local authority to ensure compliance with local construction regulations and by-laws;
liaising with clients and their representatives (architects, engineers, and surveyors), including attending regular meetings to keep them informed of progress;
day-to-day management of the site, including supervising and monitoring the site labour force and the work of any subcontractors;
planning the work and efficiently organising the plant and site facilities in order to meet deadlines;
overseeing quality control, health, and safety matters on-site;
preparing reports as required;
Resolving any unexpected technical difficulties, and other problems that may arise.
Calculate costs relating to building and civil engineering projects, from the initial calculations to the final figures.
Involved in a project from the start, preparing estimates and costs of the work.
preparing tender and contract documents, including bills of quantities with the architect and/or the client;
allocating work to subcontractors;
providing advice on contractual claims;
maintaining awareness of the different building contracts in current use;
Understanding the implications of health and safety regulations.

